<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="91" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1702,2017]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,269,1702,1728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">DNA:</emphasis>
The sequences of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rengaiyan &amp; Palayil &amp; Ingole, 2022" authorityName="Rengaiyan &amp; Palayil &amp; Ingole" authorityYear="2022" box="[480,673,1702,1728]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dendoricellidae" genus="Fibulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="occiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[480,673,1702,1728]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">Fibulia occiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[680,770,1702,1728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[680,770,1702,1728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
were submitted to NCBI GenBank and received the accession numbers: 28S 
<accessionNumber box="[371,507,1738,1764]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MW810076" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">MW810076</accessionNumber>
and 18S 
<accessionNumber box="[617,756,1738,1764]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MW810071" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">MW810071</accessionNumber>
. The 28S is 716 bp, while the 18S is 1705 bp. We have not performed a formal phylogenetic analysis since this is beyond the scope of the present paper. Nevertheless, a preliminary BLAST search indicated that these new sequences are very similar to those of poecilosclerid sponges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="92" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1702,2017]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,249]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="92" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1846,1872]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Rengaiyan &amp; Palayil &amp; Ingole, 2022" authorityName="Rengaiyan &amp; Palayil &amp; Ingole" authorityYear="2022" box="[325,519,1846,1872]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dendoricellidae" genus="Fibulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="occiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[325,519,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">Fibulia occiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[527,617,1846,1872]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[527,617,1846,1872]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is unique amongst the ten known 
<taxonomicName box="[1008,1182,1846,1872]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis box="[1008,1090,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">Fibulia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, by an arrangement of its morphology and the unique shape of the isochelae with a strongly curved shaft and well-formed frontal alae. The oxeas of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rengaiyan &amp; Palayil &amp; Ingole, 2022" authorityName="Rengaiyan &amp; Palayil &amp; Ingole" authorityYear="2022" box="[308,440,1919,1944]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dendoricellidae" genus="Fibulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="occiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[308,440,1919,1944]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">F. occiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[449,542,1918,1944]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[449,542,1918,1944]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vermiform" baseAuthorityName="Ridley &amp; Dendy" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[795,908,1919,1944]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dendoricellidae" genus="Fibulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ramosa">
<emphasis box="[795,908,1919,1944]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">F. ramosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(oxeas 450–500 µm length ×18–25 µm width and chelae 15–16 µm length) recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[665,810,1954,1980]" name="South Africa" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">South Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<quantity box="[826,946,1954,1980]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.79" metricValueMin="0.9099999999999999" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" unit="m" value="185.0" valueMax="279.0" valueMin="91.0">91–279 m</quantity>
). The oxeas size of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rengaiyan &amp; Palayil &amp; Ingole, 2022" authorityName="Rengaiyan &amp; Palayil &amp; Ingole" authorityYear="2022" box="[1176,1309,1955,1980]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dendoricellidae" genus="Fibulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="occiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1176,1309,1955,1980]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">F. occiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1317,1409,1954,1980]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1317,1409,1954,1980]" pageId="4" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is 483–(628)–700 µm in length, 14.5–(19)–21 µm in width, and the chelae size is 30–(36)–40.5 µm in length. This species was found in the deeper regions (
<quantity box="[619,778,151,177]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0305" metricValueMax="2.0789999999999997" metricValueMin="1.982" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" unit="m" value="2030.5" valueMax="2079.0" valueMin="1982.0">1982–2079 m</quantity>
) of CIOR and is geographically close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vermiform" baseAuthorityName="Ridley &amp; Dendy" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[1246,1359,151,176]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dendoricellidae" genus="Fibulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ramosa">
<emphasis box="[1246,1359,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">F. ramosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chimney" baseAuthorityName="Burton" baseAuthorityYear="1929" class="Demospongiae" family="Dendoricellidae" genus="Fibulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cribriporosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">F. cribriporosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These sponge species have been collected in the Terra Nova Bay area (
<quantity box="[1091,1227,187,213]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.585" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="0.16999999999999998" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" unit="m" value="558.5" valueMax="1100.0" valueMin="17.0">17–1,100 m</quantity>
) during the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">Italian Antarctic Expeditions</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ghiglione, C. &amp; Alvaro, M. C. &amp; Cecchetto, M. &amp; Canese, S. &amp; Downey, R. &amp; Guzzi, A. &amp; Mazzoli, C. &amp; Piazza, P. &amp; Rapp, H. T. &amp; Sara, A. &amp; Schiaparelli, S." box="[408,653,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" pagination="137 - 156" refId="ref4748" refString="Ghiglione, C., Alvaro, M. C., Cecchetto, M., Canese, S., Downey, R., Guzzi, A., Mazzoli, C., Piazza, P., Rapp, H. T., Sara, A. &amp; Schiaparelli, S. (2018) Porifera collection of the Italian national Antarctic museum (MNA), with an updated checklist from Terra Nova Bay (Ross Sea). ZooKeys, 758, 137 - 156. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 758.23485" type="journal article" year="2018">
Ghiglione 
<emphasis box="[529,585,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="92">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
